        <p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </p><h2><a name="missions" id="missions"></a>Missions</h2>
        <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
          <tr>
            <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                <tr>
                  <td height="10"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><ul>
                    <li> Agents are given special missions from time to time. They can be found in the HQ. To accept a mission, go to the HQ and click on the folder labeled &ldquo;Top Secret&rdquo; located at the bottom right screen. </li>
                    <li> To complete any mission, agents will be required to complete a series of tasks, solve problems and puzzles by using their spy tools, agent experience and knowledge of Club Penguin. </li>
                    <li> Agents who complete each mission will be rewarded. Rewards will vary depending on the nature of the mission. </li>
                    <li> Missions are periodically updated. </li>
                    </ul></td>
                </tr>
            </table></td>
            <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
            <td width="350" align="left" valign="top"><p><img src="../../images/screenshots/special-missions-.gif" width="350" height="220"></p>
                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></p>
        <h2 align="left"><a name="Take_Tour"></a><strong>Take a Tour</strong></h2>
        <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
          <tr>
            <td width="358" valign="top"><p align="left"><strong>What</strong>: Tours are a great way to get to know Club Penguin when  you&rsquo;re new to town. Tour Guides will show you different places in Club Penguin,  tell you interesting facts about the town, help you locate some games, and even  meet some friends. Once the tour is finished and you have a good grasp of the  island, penguins are encouraged to explore the island even more. There will  still be plenty to discover.</p>
              <p align="left"><strong>Where</strong>: Upon arrival in town, go to the Tour Booth. You will find it in the Ski Village.</p>
              <p align="left"><strong>Who</strong>: Tour Guides will be wearing a special Tour Guide hat  and will stand near the Tour Booth. </p>
              <p align="left"><strong>How</strong>: To join a tour, choose a guide and follow his/her  lead.&nbsp; </p>
              <p>&nbsp;</p>
              <p>&nbsp;</p>              </td>
            <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
            <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/tour-guide-1.gif" width="350" height="220"><img src="../../images/screenshots/tour-guide-2.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        
          <p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></p>
              </p>
              
			  <h2 align="left"><a name="Become_Tour_Guide"></a><strong>Become a Tour Guide</strong></h2>
              <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
          <tr>
            <td width="358" valign="top"><p align="left">Being a Tour Guide is a privileged opportunity!</p>
              <p align="left"><strong>What</strong>: A Tour Guide has the responsibility of welcoming new  arrivals to Club Penguin. It is a volunteer position and is great for penguins  who want to boost community spirit, help others and have fun at the same time. </p>
              <p align="left">A guide designs his/her own route and chooses when to work.  A Tour Guide Manual is available for guides at the Tour Booth. </p>
              <p align="left"><strong>How</strong>: To become a Tour Guide penguins must take the quiz at the  Tour Booth in the Plaza. If you answer seven of the eight questions correctly  you will be accepted as an official Tour Guide and receive a hat in your  inventory. Wear the hat when you give tours. Before you get started, read the  Tour Guide Manual. </p>
              <p align="left"><strong>Who</strong>: You need a great attitude and must be 45 days old to be  a guide.</p></td>
            <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
            <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/tour-guide-3.gif" width="350" height="220"><img src="../../images/screenshots/tour-guide-4.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        
          <p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></p>
              </p>
            <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></td>
          </tr>
